description:
One of the first big choices in The Elder Scrolls IV: Oblivion Remastered is to determine who you want to be. Are you going to be a towering Orc, swinging a massive warhammer, or maybe all powerful elven mage, burning your enemies to a crisp? #TheElderScrollsIVOblivionRemastered #Gaming #IGN

description:
A cat and a piece of buttered toast plan their great escape in this tricky puzzle-filled adventure. Watch the latest Cato: Buttered Cat trailer for a peek at their adventure ahead of the game's launch on Nintendo Switch and PS5 (PlayStation 5) on May 1, 2025. It is already available on PC.

When dropped, cats always fall on their feet, and buttered toast always falls buttered side down. But when a piece of buttered toast is attached to the back of a cat, a paradox is created, giving birth to a floating, perpetually spinning source of infinite energy!

In this game inspired by the famous buttered cat paradox that went viral on the internet, the protagonists of "cat" and "buttered toast" cooperate to escape from a labyrinth of stages filled with all sorts of puzzles.

In addition to over 140 main stages and over 60 optional stages, CATO: Buttered Cat also has a wide variety of hidden rooms, boss fights, and mini games. Collect cute costumes for your cat and toast, or even play co-op wit
title: Cato: Buttered Cat - Official Nintendo Switch and PS5 Launch Trailer

author: IGN
description:
Are you waiting for Bethesda to give Oblivion Remastered the Skyrim VR treatment? Well perhaps you don't need to! Instead, you can download a VR mod right now that turns The Elder Scrolls 4: Oblivion Remastered into a full-scale VR game that you can use with your favorite headset. With one software download, you can inject this VR mod into Oblivion and allow you to explore the newly remastered Cyrodiil in a life-like scale.

Unreal Engine VR, or UEVR, is an injecor mod by Praydog that makes it easy to take games made in the Unreal Enging and wrap them in a VR setting. This mod works with most VR headsets such as Meta Quest 3, Meta Quest 2, Valve Index, Bigsceen VR, and more. Simply choose the headset you own, and go!

#IGN #Gaming #Oblivion
title: Elder Scrolls IV: Oblivion Remastered Is Awesome in VR

When a mysterious space vessel crash-lands on Earth, a young woman and a ragtag group of tactical soldiers make a fateful discovery that puts them face-to-face with the planet’s greatest threat in the sci-fi horror series “Alien: Earth.” As members of the crash recovery crew search for survivors among the wreckage, they encounter mysterious predatory life forms more terrifying than they could have ever imagined. author: IGN
description:
Like many Bethesda games, The Elder Scrolls IV: Oblivion on PC features the ability to open a command console to input game altering cheats by pressing the Tilde key, located right here to the left of the 1 key. The PC Console Command menu is also present in Oblivion Remastered on PC, released in 2025 - however, certain codes no longer work, and others’ inputs may have changed entirely.

Here’s a few of our favorite console command cheats for your remastered adventure through Cyrodiil.

00:00 - Intro
00:45 - help (Lists commands in console editor)
00:59 - ObvGodMode or TGM (God Mode)
01:37 - PlayerSpellBook (Adds aall spells to inventory)
01:54 - ghost (Lets you fly and applies noclip)
2:21 - ToggleDebugCamera (Lets camera fly freely)
2:46 - ToggleCombatAI or tcai (Turns off NPC combat processing)
3:02 - player.payfine (Pays off bounties)
3:15 - advlevel (Forces level up)
3:36 - tmm 1 (Unlocks all map markers and fast travel points)
3:52 - unlock (Unlocks any door or chest)

#IGN #Gam
title: The Elder Scrolls IV: Oblivion Remastered - Best PC Cheats and Console Commands
